## 4. The Hand Feel Experience

- Impact Sensation
    - Hardness Words: Medium-soft feel. Although it shares the exact same 36-degree (Butterfly scale) sponge as T05, the spaced-out pimples make it feel about 2-3 degrees softer on impact.
    - Feedback: Crisp, vibrant, and highly responsive. You feel the ball hit the wood almost instantly on hard shots.
    - Hold vs. Release: Heavy emphasis on Release. The rubber wants to eject the ball immediately.
    - Dwell Time: Short. The ball does not stay on the racket long, which aids in speed and reduces spin sensitivity.

- Sound/Click
    - Produces a loud, high-pitched click or metallic crack on heavy impact, highly reminiscent of the speed glue era.

