## 5. Compatibility & Setup Guide

- Best Blade Matches
    - Outer Carbon: (e.g., Viscaria, Timo Boll ALC). Creates an absolute speed machine. Best for highly skilled attackers who play slightly off the table.
    - Inner Carbon: (e.g., Innerforce Layer ALC). An excellent pairing. The wood outer plies provide the dwell time that T64 lacks, balancing the setup perfectly.
    - All-Wood: (e.g., Korbel). Great for intermediate players wanting to harness T64's speed without losing all control in the short game.
    - Mismatch Cases: Extremely hard, stiff blades (e.g., Schlager Carbon, Primorac Carbon) combined with T64 will be completely uncontrollable for anyone below professional level.

- Forehand vs. Backhand Recommendation
    - Forehand: Good for smashers, flat hitters, or veteran players who lack the physical power to loop with hard Chinese rubbers.
    - Backhand: Highly recommended. Its low spin sensitivity, incredible blocking, and punch-counter capabilities make it a legendary backhand rubber.

